cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper deals with social media behavior and the detection of fake activities, which falls under the category of social informatics (cs.SI). The use of machine learning models for detection suggests the involvement of cyber security (cs.CYBER) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The paper also discusses the impact of fake activities on social reputation, which is related to the study of social networks (cs.SOC). Finally, the paper deals with the detection of fraudulent behavior, which is related to the study of computer security (cs.CR).
